items.title: Abercrombie & Fitch soars 27% even as retailer slashes profit outlook due to tariffs
items.description: Abercrombie & Fitch's growth is slowing at its namesake brand and the company is expecting tariffs to reduce its earnings by $50 million.

items.title: Macy's CEO says retailer will hike some prices as tariffs cut into profits
items.description: Macy's beat earnings estimates for the first quarter, but cut its 2025 profit outlook as tariffs complicate its turnaround strategy.

items.title: Dick's Sporting Goods stands by full-year guidance — even with tariffs looming
items.description: Dick's Sporting Goods reaffirmed its sales and profit guidance for fiscal 2025 and said the figures take into account all current tariffs in effect.

items.title: Goldman-backed Starling Bank reports 26% profit drop as it flags Covid loan fraud issue
items.description: British neobank Starling posted an annual profit before tax of £223.4 million, down nearly 26% year-on-year.

items.title: Okta shares plunge 11% as company maintains guidance, citing macroeconomic uncertainties
items.description: Okta reported better-than-expected earnings and revenue in its quarterly report on Tuesday but kept its guidance.
